It&#8217;s been almost 18 months since the Nelson Mandela Bay&#8217;s corporate services boss Mod Ndoyana was suspended, and he was finally fired on Tuesday.This is following a lengthy disciplinary process, started by the former mayor Danny Jordaan.Ndoyana was accused of gross negligence, violations of municipal law and various irregularities. This is the second high profile case that has been successfully prosecuted and includes the recent dismissal of supply chain management employee, Sox Nkanjeni, says Councillor Dean Biddulph. We intend to clean up the administration without fear or favour and remain on course to create a model of governance where accountability, honesty and professionalism become the hallmarks of a people-centred local government, Source:HeraldLive